# Documentation freshness

Docs are part of every change. Before opening a PR, audit each doc that
mirrors what changed and update it in the same PR — never as a follow-up.

## What to check (and where it mirrors)

- Schema changes in `packages/core/src/planInputs.ts` →
  `docs/architecture.md` §4.1 (the `PlanInputs` table and any sub-tables
  for discriminated-union variants like `LifeEvent`).
- `@app/core` public API (new export, signature change) →
  `docs/architecture.md` §2.3.
- Env vars added/removed/renamed → `.env.example` AND the env Zod schema
  in `app/src/lib/env.ts` / `env.server.ts` AND `docs/architecture.md` §6.
- Routes / API endpoints added → `docs/architecture.md` §2.2 bullet list.
- Stack / scripts changes (new package, new script, deploy step) →
  `README.md`.
- Milestone progress (a milestone ships) → `ROADMAP.md` checkbox + change log.
- Feature shipped via plan mode → archive the plan to
  `docs/plans/YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.md` and add a one-line entry in
  `docs/plans/README.md` (bumping the plan-count line).

## When you change `docs/architecture.md`

Run `npm run docs:build` to regenerate `docs/architecture.pdf` and
`docs/architecture.html`, then commit all three files together — the
`docs/README.md` explicitly calls this out.

## Report explicitly

In the final pre-ship summary (and in the PR body), list each doc you
checked and whether it was updated or confirmed unchanged. "I forgot" is
not an allowed state.
